# Problem: Code cannot distinguish between the ball moving UP and the camera moving DOWN.
# Impact: Handheld footage is currently unusable for accurate vector analysis.
# Solution: Use the "Planted Foot" (static anchor) as a reference point to subtract camera global motion from ball local motion.

# [LOW] 5. FPS INDEPENDENCY (HARD-CODED LOOKBACK)
# Problem: LOOKBACK = 10 assumes 30/60 FPS. 
# Impact: Analysis will fail or lag on 240 FPS (Slow-Mo) footage.
# Solution: Refactor LOOKBACK as a function of cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FPS).

